      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T15:05:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Honestly either of these choices sounds better to me than reintroducing `mutable`:\n\n- tracking the initial values in some context structure external to the Variable\n- restructuring the calls to IRGenerator so that the DSL handles the creation of the Variable (which would be fairly unnatural)\n\nCan we at least give these ideas a try? I think keeping our const-correctness intact is worth the extra effort.",
      "parentUuid": "2e5a8fc9_914bbc7a",
